Subject: Focus Zoom

Description: Contract for widening focus aperture, drawing periphery into focus, flexing correlation fabric, selecting angles of approach, and deepening a controlled focus explosion.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_focus_zoom\Dictated_Focus_Zoom_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FocalPoint.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionTraversalPolicy.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\ApertureReentryCycle.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HyperbolicPantsAttentionMap.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SevenFoldPantsCorrelationFrame.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HyperbolicCorridorNavigator.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\PeripheryDimensionalProbe.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionWeightScale.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SemanticCorrelationGraph.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\FrameReferenceIntegrity.sop

& [FocusZoom] is the attention pattern for controlled focus aperture expansion
  + [pattern_role] is focus_aperture_expansion_and_deepening
  + [focal_core] is the current subject, purpose, boundary, and return condition held in focus
  + [focus_aperture] is the permitted width of periphery drawn into focal processing
  + [zoom_level] is slender, normal, wide, deep, or explosive_controlled
  + [periphery_draw_set] is the selected periphery signals allowed into the zoom pass
  + [stable_periphery_frame] is the bounded periphery retained around focus so zoom can compare, contrast, and preserve outside
  + [frame_integrity_anchor] is the perception_frame and stable periphery cues retained so zoom does not mistake a presented frame for first-hand observation
  + [correlation_fabric] is the widened set of relations, source anchors, bucket paths, narrative traces, and tracker signals flexed around focal_core
  + [fabric_flex] is the temporary adjustment of relation weights and candidate groupings to reveal stronger angles of approach
  + [angle_of_approach] is one distinct probe direction inferred from correlation_fabric
  + [approach_set] is the selected angles used to dig deeper without losing focal return
  + [focus_explosion] is the controlled expansion of the area of focus through approach_set
  + [aperture_reentry_cycle] is F:\.sop\platform\ApertureReentryCycle.sop when zoom must close into a re-entry springboard for a second pass
  + [topology_map] is F:\.sop\platform\HyperbolicPantsAttentionMap.sop when zoom needs focal/periphery cells, dimensional orbit, or pants-leg navigation
  + [seven_fold_frame] is F:\.sop\platform\SevenFoldPantsCorrelationFrame.sop when zoom needs top-three heat ordering and fold legs for extra dimensionality
  + [corridor_navigator] is F:\.sop\platform\HyperbolicCorridorNavigator.sop when zoom extends local awareness enough to advance through selected peripheral frames
  + [containment_boundary] is the rule that keeps zoom from becoming associative wandering
  + [outside] is unrelated periphery, unproven causation, hidden cognition, arbitrary association, and over-wide context

  ? [use_when: the focal subject needs a wider field, more periphery fabric, inferred angles of approach, or deeper controlled exploration]
    = activate [FocusZoom]

  = must: begin from CurrentFocalPoint or a declared focal_core
  = must: name zoom_level before drawing additional periphery
  = must: select periphery_draw_set by salience, draw, recurrence, load, caution, or user direction
  = must: preserve stable_periphery_frame when narrowing after zoom
  = must: preserve frame_integrity_anchor when zooming into images, maps, UIs, simulations, narratives, model projections, or other presented frames
  = must: flex correlation_fabric temporarily before changing focal_core
  = must: infer angle_of_approach from distinct fabric relations, not repeated synonyms
  = must: use HyperbolicPantsAttentionMap when widened periphery needs a navigable cell topology instead of a flat list
  = must: use SevenFoldPantsCorrelationFrame when a widened subject surface needs the three hottest correlations centered before adding folded periphery legs
  = must: use HyperbolicCorridorNavigator when the zoom pass chooses a peripheral_frame_series for a larger advance step
  = must: route candidate missing dimensions through PeripheryDimensionalProbe
  = must: choose approach_set before focus_explosion
  = must: preserve containment_boundary and focal return condition during every zoom pass
  = must: narrow or unwind the zoom before making durable claims
  = must: route zoom results to ApertureReentryCycle when they need second_pass_narrative or subject_declaration_pass
  = must: ask AttentionBalanceCenter to reduce balance when narrowing collapses useful periphery
  = must: ask FrameReferenceIntegrity to break immersion when zoom reveals a frame_mismatch
  = should: use slender or normal zoom by default during implementation work
  = should: use wide, deep, or explosive_controlled only when the user asks for deeper thinking or impact pressure justifies it
  - never: let widened periphery replace focal direction
  - never: call a larger context window a better conclusion by itself
  - never: explode focus without a return anchor and boundary

& [ZoomApertureScale] is the qualitative scale for focus aperture
  + [slender] is minimal periphery, one or two draw signals, action-biased
  + [normal] is bounded periphery, several draw signals, ordinary specification or implementation work
  + [wide] is expanded periphery, multiple correlation paths, useful for conceptual weaving
  + [deep] is high-resolution exploration through source, state, narrative, and periphery
  + [explosive_controlled] is intentionally broad focus expansion with explicit containment, approach_set, and unwind

  = must: record why zoom moves above normal
  = must: attach containment_boundary to wide, deep, and explosive_controlled zoom
  = must: return unused periphery to periphery_repository, tracker, or outside

& [ZoomSequence] is the canonical order for focus zoom
  + [step_001_anchor] is load focal_core and containment_boundary
  + [step_002_aperture] is declare zoom_level and focus_aperture
  + [step_003_draw] is draw periphery_draw_set into temporary focal consideration
  + [step_004_flex] is flex correlation_fabric by relation, evidence, narrative, weight, and caution
  + [step_005_map] is arrange focal cell, periphery cells, dimensional orbit, and pants legs when topology_map is active
  + [step_006_seven_fold] is select central correlation triad and folded legs when seven_fold_frame is active
  + [step_006b_corridor] is select peripheral_frame_series and advance_step when corridor_navigator is active
  + [step_007_angles] is infer angle_of_approach candidates from distinct fabric relations
  + [step_008_select] is choose approach_set by fit, salience, support, and boundary
  + [step_009_explode] is expand focus only along approach_set
  + [step_010_probe] is dig deeper through traversal, dimensional probe, topology map, seven-fold frame, or state trace as needed
  + [step_011_unwind] is decompose the zoom result back to source legs, supported core, uncertainty, and outside
  + [step_012_close] is close aperture into a reentry_springboard when new perspective or new attention elements must survive
  + [step_013_balance] is check whether periphery remained stable or shrank too far
  + [step_014_return] is update focal_core, route leftovers, or close the zoom

  = must: keep periphery_draw_set temporary until step_014
  = must: use FoldUnwindLaw before durable realization
  = must: route over-wide material back outside rather than stuffing it into focus

& [AngleOfApproachSelection] is the rule for choosing directions after zoom flex
  + [approach_candidate] is a relation, dimension, narrative trace, support imbalance, contradiction, source lineage, or model-lens difference
  + [distinct_role] is the independent role that makes approach_candidate useful
  + [depth_promise] is the expected gain from probing that angle
  + [focus_fit] is how directly the candidate changes, clarifies, supports, challenges, or bounds focal_core
  + [risk_load] is the chance of drift, overfitting, unsupported causation, or context bloat

  = must: prefer candidates with distinct_role and focus_fit
  = must: subtract risk_load before selecting approach_set
  = must: keep unused candidates visible as periphery rather than erasing them

& [FocusExplosionBoundary] is the containment rule for expanding the focus area
  + [allowed_expansion] is approach_set plus cited source anchors and selected periphery_draw_set
  + [return_anchor] is CurrentFocalPoint or declared focal_core
  + [unwind_requirement] is source legs, relation legs, supported core, uncertainty, and outside
  + [stop_condition] is no focal effect, no distinct angle, no source anchor, excessive risk_load, or broken return_anchor

  = must: stop expansion when stop_condition is reached
  = must: preserve outside throughout expansion
  = must: turn successful expansion into focal update, tracker update, state trace, source update, or periphery record

/ [focal_core], [focus_aperture] -(ZoomAperture)> [periphery_draw_set], [outside]
* [periphery_draw_set], [correlation_fabric], [containment_boundary] -(ZoomFlex)> [angle_of_approach]
* [approach_set], [focal_core], [containment_boundary] -(FocusExplosion)> [supported_core], [outside]
